<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1419] Expert API to specify indexing chain</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1419</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be nice to add an expert API to specify an indexing chain, so that&lt;br/&gt;
we can make use of Mike&apos;s nice &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1301&quot; title=&quot;Refactor DocumentsWriter&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1301&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; feature.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch simply adds a package-protected expert API to IndexWriter and &lt;br/&gt;
DocumentsWriter. It adds a inner, abstract class to DocumentsWriter called &lt;br/&gt;
IndexingChain, and a default implementation that is the currently used one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This might not be the final solution, but a nice way to play with different&lt;br/&gt;
modules in the indexing chain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you take a look at the patch, Mike? &lt;/p&gt;</description>
